  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ Gas 7</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>conchiglie</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a large pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>conchiglie</strong> for an initial 4-5 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-cauliflower-mac-n-cheese/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>cauliflower stalk<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop the <strong>cauliflower head<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>into small florets</p><p>Add 200g <span class=\"text-danger\">[400g]</span> of <strong>cauliflower florets </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) to the pot with the <strong>conchiglie</strong> and cook for a further 4-5 min or until everything is cooked through and tender</p><p>Once done, drain and set aside in the colander</p><p>Reserve the pot for later</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-cauliflower-mac-n-cheese/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and roughly chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and roughly chop the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve the <strong>veg stock mix</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-cauliflower-mac-n-cheese/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped onion </strong>and <strong>garlic </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Add the <strong>veg stock</strong> with 200g<span class=\"text-danger\"> [400g] </span>of the <strong>reserved</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>cauliflower stalks </strong>and <strong>florets </strong>to the pot and cook for 8-10 min until softened</p><p>Tip: Roast any remaining cauliflower with some spices for a tasty snack!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-cauliflower-mac-n-cheese/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, remove the pot from heat and add the <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>cauliflower mixture</strong></p><p>Blitz the <strong>cauliflower mixture</strong> with a<strong> (stick) blender</strong> until smooth – this is your<strong> cauliflower sauce</strong></p><p>Tip: Alternatively, transfer everything to a food processor and blitz!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-cauliflower-mac-n-cheese/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>drained pasta & cauliflower</strong> to the pot with the<strong> cauliflower sauce </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Transfer to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> and top with <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until bubbling and golden</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-cauliflower-mac-n-cheese/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the<strong> cherry tomatoes </strong>into quarters</p><p>Wash the <strong>rocket</strong>, then pat it dry with <strong>kitchen paper </strong>and add it to a large bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped cherry tomatoes </strong>and <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>to the rocket and gently mix together – this is your <strong>balsamic dressed salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-cauliflower-mac-n-cheese/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Leave the <strong>cauliflower mac 'n' cheese</strong> to stand for 5 min before serving</p><p>Serve the<strong> cauliflower mac 'n' cheese </strong>with the <strong>balsamic dressed salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
